To investigate the relationship between wavelength (\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}lambda}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}), slit width (\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{a}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}), and the width of the central maximum (\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{W}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}) in a single\PYGZhy{}slit diffraction pattern, and to use the experimental data to verify the diffraction formula.

\PYG{k}{\PYGZbs{}section*}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}}\PYG{k}{\PYGZbs{}textcolor}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}}MainBlue\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZcb{}\PYGZob{}}Theory \PYG{k}{\PYGZbs{}\PYGZam{}} Diagram\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZcb{}\PYGZcb{}}

When light passes through a narrow slit of width \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{a}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}, it bends and interferes, creating a diffraction pattern. The distance from the center to the first dark fringe (minimum) is given by \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{y}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}. The total width of the central maximum (\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{W}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}) is \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{l+m}{2}\PYG{n+nb}{y}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}.

\PYG{l+s+sb}{\PYGZbs{}[}\PYG{n+nb}{ W }\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}frac}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}}\PYG{l+m}{2}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}lambda}\PYG{n+nb}{ D\PYGZcb{}\PYGZob{}a\PYGZcb{} }\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZbs{}]}

Where: \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}lambda}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}text}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}wavelength\PYGZcb{}}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}, \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{D }\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}text}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}screen distance\PYGZcb{}}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}, and \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{a }\PYG{o}{=}\PYG{n+nb}{ }\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}text}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}slit width\PYGZcb{}}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}.

