2. Adjust the sliders for \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nv}{\PYGZbs{}lambda}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}, \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{a}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}, and \PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}}\PYG{n+nb}{D}\PYG{l+s}{\PYGZdl{}} according to the observation table.

3. Use the draggable \PYG{k}{\PYGZbs{}textbf}\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZob{}}Precision Ruler\PYG{n+nb}{\PYGZcb{}} to measure the total width of the Central Bright Fringe.

4. Record your measurements and calculate the theoretical value to find the \PYG{k}{\PYGZbs{}\PYGZpc{}} Error.

